	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The Baslisk Bracer comes off of a Baslisk.  It's that simple.  If you can get to the Lavastorm Mountains without dying (KOS through Nektulos) then you will come upon a magma rich plane filled with wonderous magic weapon only creatures.  There are fire elementals (have fire shield), rock dervs (drop ore for you blacksmiths), fire imps (tough, but a nuisance), fire drakes (have nice sparkly gems), and the Baslisk.  The Baslisk is a fire attack creature too, so make sure you have your shielding.  For a level 10 group, one of these is pretty tough.  They also stun, so beware if you are pulling.  There is a ruin (can't remember name) that inside of it is a zone, so fight there in case you meet a couple nasties at once.  Anyway, I have fought Baslisks on several occassions with someone wanting the Bracer.  It never spawned in three days of playing, but the xp you get there and the pp is great.  This was the first time I dropped 1700 cp and 900 sp just because it weighed me down.  It was great.  If you have someone that can summon an interdimensional (?) bag that allow you to store 4 things without weight penalty, that can help.  Hope this answered your question.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
